web.controller.communication.websockets

Class WebSocketCommunication

  • java.lang.Object
    • web.controller.communication.websockets.WebSocketCommunication
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WebCommunication

    public class WebSocketCommunication
extends Object
implements WebCommunication
    This class defines the WebSocket Endpoint. This implementation recognizes WS-Calls on /representation path and is defined for four subprotocols namely CREATE, UPDATE, READ and DELETE.
    Author:
    Jan-Peter.Schmidt

      • processUpload

        public void processUpload(ByteBuffer msg,
                          boolean last,
                          javax.websocket.Session session)
        This method is used for clients that want to upload files to the framework while using a operation. Files are converted to a @link{java.io.File, File} and afterwards sent to the framework by calling the selected operation.
        Parameters:
        msg - Current part of upload
        last - Flag, if end of datastream
        session - Current session.

      • onMessage

        public void onMessage(javax.websocket.Session session,
                      String message)
               throws IOException
        This method is called when a client sents a message. By checking the agreeed subprotocol the method knows which operation the user has excecuted and calls the corresponding method.
        Parameters:
        session - Current session
        message - Message that the user has sent.
        Throws:
        IOException - Throws IOException on error.
